--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages tcpreplay.

Tcpreplay is a tool to replay captured network traffic. Currently, tcpreplay
supports pcap (tcpdump) and snoop capture formats. Also included, is tcpprep
a tool to pre-process capture files to allow increased performance under
certain conditions as well as capinfo which provides basic information about
capture files.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: tcpreplay
       tcpreplay_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: tcpreplay
       tcpreplay_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  tcpreplay_state
    Specify predetermined 'tcpreplay_state' variable (string).

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

